intro: Cupania cunninghamii, commonly known as the Cunningham's cupania, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It belongs to the Euphorbiaceae family and is characterized by its small, green, oval-shaped leaves. The plant produces clusters of yellowish-green flowers that are often overlooked due to their modest appearance. It thrives in a variety of soil types but prefers well-drained conditions. Cupania cunninghamii is often found in woodland and heathland environments, contributing to the biodiversity of its native habitat.
